        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/hegseth-brawner-honor-guards-camp-aguinaldo-philippines-defense.png" alt="US Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth and Philippine Army Chief of Staff Romeo Brawner Jr. inspected honor guards at Camp Aguinaldo in the Philippines" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>US Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth and Philippine Army Chief of Staff Romeo Brawner Jr. inspected honor guards at Camp Aguinaldo in the Philippines. Credits: Lisa Marie David/Reuters</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          China launched <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-02-04-2025-h1-1-large-scale-military-drills" target="_blank">large-scale military drills</a> around Taiwan as a ‚Äústern warning‚Äù following US Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth‚Äôs vow to counter China‚Äôs aggression in Asia. The exercises, involving China‚Äôs army, navy, air force, and rocket force, simulate assaults and blockades around Taiwan, which China claims as its own.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Taiwan condemned the drills as reckless and placed its military on high alert. This is not the first drill of its kind. China has intensified military pressure on Taiwan in recent years. China often engages in encirclement exercises while accusing Taiwan‚Äôs President Lai Ching-te of separatism.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Taiwanese officials see the drills as Beijing‚Äôs response to increasing US military focus on the Indo-Pacific. China wants to maintain its hegemony in this region. Hegseth‚Äôs visit to Japan and the Philippines reaffirmed the US commitment to regional security, pressuring China ahead of upcoming trade talks.</p>
        </mj-text>
