        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Somaliland shuns Somalia</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/port-berbera-somalia-somaliland-puntland-map-geography.png" alt="The port of Berbera and the land mass showcasing Somalia, Somaliland, and Puntland" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>The port of Berbera and the land mass showcasing Somalia, Somaliland, and Puntland. Credits: British International Investment and Al Jazeera</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Somaliland has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-02-04-2025-h2-2-rejected-somalis-offer" target="_blank">rejected Somalia‚Äôs offer</a> to give the US exclusive control of the Berbera port and airbase, stating that Mogadishu (Somalia‚Äôs capital) has no authority over its territory. In a letter to President Trump, Somalia‚Äôs President Hassan Sheikh Mohamud offered access to four ports, including Berbera, claiming it would <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-02-04-2025-h2-3-enhance-us-security" target="_blank">enhance US security</a> and limit foreign influence in the Horn of Africa.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Somaliland‚Äôs foreign minister called the move ‚Äúdesperate‚Äù and expressed confidence that the US will soon recognize Somaliland‚Äôs independence. Somalia, meanwhile, is concerned that Trump might reduce US military support against the militant group Al-Shabaab, the country‚Äôs main security threat.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Although Somalia claims Somaliland as part of its sovereign territory, it has no actual control over the region. The latter declared independence in 1991.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
