        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Russia pushes more conscripts</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: Putin to conscript 160,000 more Russians for war with Ukraine despite the calls for peace</strong></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Putin has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-02-04-2025-h3-4-ordered-the-conscription" target="_blank">ordered the conscription</a> of 160,000 more Russian citizens into the military between April 1 and July 15, despite ongoing ceasefire negotiations with Ukraine. The Kremlin has assured that conscripts won‚Äôt be sent to combat, but many are coerced into signing contracts and deployed. So why more troops despite peacemaking efforts?</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Zelenskyy believes that Russia is stalling peace talks while preparing new offensives in Sumy, Kharkiv, and Zaporizhzhia. He argues that Putin wants to negotiate from a position of strength and remains focused solely on continuing the war. President Trump, on the other hand, believes that Putin wants peace but criticized Putin‚Äôs demand to remove Zelenskyy from power.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Independent Russian journalists have verified over 100,000 Russian military deaths, while Ukraine estimates nearly one million Russian casualties. Early in the war, a major issue was the lack of training among Russian conscripts. Additionally, <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-02-04-2025-h3-5-ethnic-minorities" target="_blank">ethnic minorities</a> from poorer Russian republics were conscripted at disproportionately high rates.</p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>
