        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">What is the Confucius Institute?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/australian-universities-cut-ties-china-confucius-institutes-scrutiny.png" alt="Six Australian Universities Cut Ties With China-Linked Confucius Institutes Amid Scrutiny" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Six Australian Universities Cut Ties With China-Linked Confucius Institutes Amid Scrutiny. Credits: en.Econostrum.info - Australia</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-02-04-2025-f1-8-confucius-institute" target="_blank">Confucius Institute</a> (CI) is a Chinese government-funded group that promotes the Chinese language and culture worldwide. Established in 2004, the CIs have been run by the Center for Language Education and Cooperation since 2020. Its primary goals are promoting the Chinese language overseas and deepening the understanding of its culture worldwide.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">As of 2023, 498 Confucius Institutes and 773 Confucius Classrooms had been established in over 160 countries and regions. The mission of CIs isn‚Äôt inherently political. CIs offer Chinese classes, host cultural events, and organize scholarships for students to study in China.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Critics say Confucius Institutes act as propaganda tools for the Chinese Communist Party. They influence academic talks by clarifying topics like Tibet, Taiwan, Xinjiang, and Tiananmen Square. Some also fear Chinese government control, possible espionage, and limits on academic freedom.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Many other institutes, such as Alliance Francais (France) and the Goethe Institute (Germany), do similar things to the CI. The CI asserts that it is just fostering international friendship and cultural exchange. Supporters of CIS write off criticism as Sinophobia and cite that these other organizations do not get discriminated against. </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
